messages.content:
Hello! I hope this message finds you well. Can’t help but notice that you rarely actually respond to me, but I understand that to be a result of your disposition and the lack of urgent necessity to reply to me if nothing is wrong.

It is two days until the beginning of The Antarctica Project by my count. I hope we’re at least synchronized on that point. Hope everything is going smoothly, etc etc. The real reason I’m reaching out is because there’s something you ought to know about the project. Specifically regarding the amount of participants. It’s probably not wise to go into specifics here, but this is something you ought to know and this is a place I know you check.

That’s all. Just reach out to me and I’ll let you know what’s going on. Toodleoo, farewell, see you soon.
